PEDIATRIC EMERGENCY CARE APPLIED RESEARCH NETWORK (PECARN) - PROJECT TITLE:   SPARC – SAN FRANCISCO-OAKLAND, PROVIDENCE, ATLANTA RESEARCH COLLABORATIVE;                        A CATEGORY 1 APPLICATION IN RESPONSE TO THE HRSA-19-052 FUNDING OPPORTUNITY APPLICANT:       CLAUDIA R. MORRIS, MD, FAAP ORGANIZATION:  EMORY UNIVERSITY ADDRESS:         1760 HAYGOOD DRIVE NE, W458, ATLANTA, GA  30322 PHONE:            OFFICE: (404) 727-5500;  FAX: (000) 000-0000 E-MAIL:            CLAUDIA.R.MORRIS@EMORY.EDU        FUNDS REQUESTED: $700,000 PER YEAR, FOR 4 YEARS  PROBLEM: THE GAPS IN KNOWLEDGE AND CHALLENGES OF HIGH QUALITY EMERGENCY MEDICAL SERVICES FOR CHILDREN (EMSC) RESEARCH INCLUDE: 1) LOW INCIDENCE OF MANY PEDIATRIC EMERGENCIES; 2) HEALTH INEQUITIES; 3) THE DEARTH OF PRE-HOSPITAL STUDIES; 4) THE NEED FOR RIGOROUS RESEARCH METHODS, A HIGHLY PRODUCTIVE AND COLLABORATIVE RESEARCH INFRASTRUCTURE, AND ROBUST CLINICAL DATA CAPTURE WITH LINKAGE TO PATIENT OUTCOMES; AND 5) THE TRANSLATION, IMPLEMENTATION AND WIDE DISSEMINATION OF RESEARCH FINDINGS ACROSS THE SPECTRUM OF EMERGENCY PROVIDERS AND SETTINGS.  GOALS AND OBJECTIVES: GOALS: A) PRIORITIZE HEALTH EQUITY; B) MAINTAIN ROBUST ED AND PREHOSPITAL RESEARCH INFRASTRUCTURE; C) CONDUCT HIGH QUALITY, HIGH IMPACT, RIGOROUS EMSC RESEARCH; D) DEVELOP INNOVATIVE, FUNDABLE NETWORK PROJECTS; E) DISSEMINATE EVIDENCED-BASED KNOWLEDGE AND PRACTICES TO ALL EMSC CLINICIANS; F) FOSTER EARLY STAGE INVESTIGATORS. SPECIFIC OBJECTIVES INCLUDE: 1) MAINTAIN A PRODUCTIVE NODE AND EMSA (EMS AFFILIATE); 2) ENROLL HIGH PERCENTAGES OF ELIGIBLE PARTICIPANTS; 3) MEET OR EXCEED PECARN QUALITY CONTROL OBJECTIVES (E.G. TIMELY COLLECTION AND SUBMISSION OF DATA, RESOLUTION OF DATA QUERIES, SAFETY MONITORING/REPORTING, ETC.); 4) SUBMIT  AT LEAST ONE PECARN CONCEPT PER YEAR, AND ONE PROTOCOL EVERY 2 YEARS; 5) DEVELOP AT LEAST ONE PRE-HOSPITAL RESEARCH PROPOSAL; 6) CONTINUE CONTRIBUTING OVER 250,000 HEALTH RECORDS ANNUALLY TO THE PECARN REGISTRY, FROM A GEOGRAPHICALLY UNDERREPRESENTED AREA OF THE NETWOR K; 7) CONTINUE EMS DATA LINKAGE EFFORTS; 8) DISSEMINATE EMSC RESEARCH FINDINGS BROADLY; AND 9) MENTOR AND SUPPORT JUNIOR FACULTY MEMBERS.    EVALUATION:  WE WILL REGULARLY MONITOR OUR NODE’S PROGRESS BASED ON THE SPECIFIC OBJECTIVES DESCRIBED ABOVE, AND THE ASSOCIATED TIMELINES DESCRIBED IN OUR APPLICATION. WE WILL ALSO MONITOR AND REPORT OUR CLINICAL RESEARCH PRODUCTIVITY, BASED ON PECARN ENROLLMENT AND DATA METRICS.  DISSEMINATION AND KNOWLEDGE TRANSFER WILL BE MEASURED IN MULTIPLE WAYS, E.G. PRESENTATIONS, PUBLICATIONS, AND AN EXPANDED SOCIAL MEDIA PRESENCE. METHODOLOGY:  SPARC WILL CONTINUE TO CAPITALIZE ON THEIR PI’S EXTENSIVE RESEARCH EXPERIENCE, FEDERAL FUNDING FOR, LEADERSHIP OF AND ROBUST ENROLLMENT IN PECARN STUDIES. SPARC WILL VIEW ALL RESEARCH THROUGH A HEALTH EQUITY LENS. SPARC IS WELL POSITIONED TO CONTINUE ITS HIGH PERFORMANCE IN NETWORK STANDARDS AND EXPECTATIONS.  COORDINATION:  SPARC WILL CONTINUE TO USE REGULAR TELECONFERENCING TO REVIEW NODAL AND NETWORK STUDY METRICS, TO COORDINATE OUR ACTIVITIES, FOSTER CAREERS OF NEW INVESTIGATORS FOCUSING ON THOSE UNDERREPRESENTED IN MEDICINE, AND DISCUSS NEW CONCEPTS. WE WILL PARTICIPATE IN ALL PECARN NETWORK MEETINGS AND ACTIVITIES, WORKING WITH STUDY PIS, THE EDC, AND OTHER NODES TO ASSURE SEAMLESS COLLABORATIONS. LASTLY, WE WILL ACTIVELY INTERFACE WITH LOCAL, REGIONAL AND NATIONAL HEALTH AND PROFESSIONAL ORGANIZATIONS INVOLVED IN CARING FOR PEDIATRIC EMERGENCIES.   ANNOTATION:  SPARC IS A COLLABORATIVE OF PEDIATRIC EMERGENCY MEDICINE RESEARCHERS AT EMORY, BROWN, AND UCSF, WITH PARTICULAR EXPERTISE IN UNDER-INVESTIGATED EMSC CONDITIONS, I.E. HEALTHCARE DISPARITIES, SICKLE CELL DISEASE, BEHAVIORAL HEALTH, SUBSTANCE USE DISORDERS, DISSEMINATION, AND PRE-HOSPITAL DATA.

EMSC PARTNERSHIP GRANTS - STATE OF OHIO 1 PROJECT ABSTRACT PROJECT TITLE: EMERGENCY MEDICAL SERVICES FOR CHILDREN STATE PARTNERSHIP PROGRAM – OHIO APPLICANT ORGANIZATION NAME: NATIONWIDE CHILDREN’S HOSPITAL/ DEPARTMENT OF PEDIATRICS, THE OHIO STATE UNIVERSITY COLLEGE OF MEDICINE ADDRESS: 700 CHILDREN'S DRIVE, COLUMBUS, OH 43205 PROJECT DIRECTOR NAME: JULIE C. LEONARD, MD MPH PHONE/FAX: (614) 355-5860 EMAIL ADDRESS: JULIE.LEONARD@NATIONWIDECHILDRENS.ORG WEBSITE ADDRESS: HTTPS://WWW.EMS.OHIO.GOV/EMSC.ASPX GRANT PROGRAM FUNDS REQUESTED: $205,000/ YEAR THE PURPOSE OF THE OHIO EMS FOR CHILDREN STATE PARTNERSHIP PROGRAM IS TO IMPROVE ACCESS AND QUALITY OF EMERGENCY CARE FOR CHILDREN AND REDUCE SERIOUS INJURY AND ILLNESS. THE PROGRAM WILL IMPROVE OHIO’S ABILITY TO CARE FOR ACUTELY ILL AND INJURED CHILDREN BY FOCUSING ON IMPROVED PEDIATRIC EMERGENCY CARE COORDINATION IN EMERGENCY DEPARTMENTS AND EMS AGENCIES, DEVELOPING BOTH PREHOSPITAL AND HOSPITAL BASED PEDIATRIC READINESS RECOGNITION PROGRAMS, FURTHER DEVELOPING OUR STATEWIDE DISASTER PREPAREDNESS FOR PEDIATRIC PATIENTS, AND FURTHER PARTNERING WITH FAMILY REPRESENTATIVES. PROGRESS WILL BE MEASURED AGAINST NATIONAL PERFORMANCE MEASURES AND PROGRAM OBJECTIVES ESTABLISHED BY HRSA. $205,000 IN ANNUAL FUNDING IS REQUESTED OVER FOUR YEARS TO SUPPORT AN EMSC PROGRAM MANAGER AND PROJECT DIRECTOR, AS WELL AS PROVIDING THE NECESSARY FUNDS TO PROVIDE EDUCATIONAL SUPPLIES AND OPPORTUNITIES TO STATEWIDE EMS AND ED COMMUNITY PARTNERS, AND TO HOST AN ANNUAL OHIO EMSC EDUCATIONAL CONFERENCE. OUR AREAS OF FOCUS WILL BE EXPANSION AND SUPPORT OF PEDIATRIC EMERGENCY CARE COORDINATION AND DISASTER PREPAREDNESS, AS WELL AS PROGRAM SUSTAINABILITY. OVER THE FOUR YEARS OF THE GRANT, WE AIM TO MEET OR EXCEED NATIONAL PERFORMANCE MEASURE TARGETS.
